pipeline_summary.name: Database Partition Check ETL
pipeline_summary.description: Sensor-gated daily ETL pipeline that waits for database partition availability before extracting, transforming, and loading incremental orders data.

components.name: Wait for Daily Partition
components.description: Checks the information_schema.partitions table until the daily partition for the orders table exists, then emits a success signal to unlock the ETL workflow.

upstream_policy.description: No upstream dependencies; this sensor starts the pipeline.

connections.purpose: Read partition metadata from source database

components.name: Extract Incremental Orders
components.description: Reads new orders from the daily partition of the orders table, filtered by the current date, and outputs the raw incremental dataset.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after the partition sensor succeeds.

connections.purpose: Read incremental orders from source database

components.name: Transform Orders Data
components.description: Cleans, validates, and enriches the extracted orders data (e.g., customer names, addresses, amounts, timestamps) preparing it for loading.

upstream_policy.description: Executes after successful extraction of incremental orders.

components.name: Load Orders to Warehouse
components.description: Writes the transformed orders data into the fact_orders table of the target data warehouse and updates related metrics.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after successful transformation of orders data.

connections.purpose: Write transformed orders to target warehouse

description.default: Sensor-gated daily ETL pipeline that waits for database partition availability before extracting, transforming, and loading incremental orders data.

batch_window.description: Batch window parameter name (e.g., ds, execution_date)

partitioning.description: Data partitioning strategy (e.g., daily, hourly, monthly)

depends_on_past.description: Whether execution depends on previous run success

timeout.description: Maximum time in seconds the sensor will wait

poke_interval.description: Time in seconds between sensor checks

sources: Daily partition of the `orders` table in the source relational database (filtered by CURRENT_DATE)
sinks: `fact_orders` table in the target data warehouse
